.TH "ubifs_prepare_node" 9 "ubifs_prepare_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_prepare_node \- prepare node to be written to flash.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ubifs_prepare_node
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "void *node "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int pad "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "node" 12
the node to pad
.IP "len" 12
node length
.IP "pad" 12
if the buffer has to be padded
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function prepares node at \fInode\fP to be written to the media - it
calculates node CRC, fills the common header, and adds proper padding up to
the next minimum I/O unit if \fIpad\fP is not zero.
